\pard \fs24\qj\tx-540\tx0\tx720\tx1440\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\tx5040\tx5760\tx6480\tx7200\tx7920\tx8640\tx8910\tx9360\tx10080\tx10800\tx11520\tx12240\tx12960\tx13680\tx14400\tx15120\tx15840\tx16560\tx17280\tx18000\tx18720 
{\plain \fs24 \b\f8 New Adult Sunday School Series  - Back to the Basics, Starting December 2.  }{\plain \fs24 \f8 Please join us for a new Adult \softline
Sunday School Series, "Back to the Basics".  We will explore some of those foundational, basic Christian teachings \softline
that you may have learned long ago in Sunday school or confirmation.  However, we will explore them from 
different angles, see how they compare with views from other denominations, and do a deeper dive of certain \softline
aspects of these teachings.  We will start our series with a discussion about the Sacrament of Holy Communion.  \softline
Do all denominations believe in the true presence of the body and blood of Jesus Christ in this sacrament?  Do \softline
all denominations have the same reason for the purpose and efficacy of this sacrament?  We will explore these \softline
and many other questions. We will welcome those who have never learned about this topic.  We welcome those \softline
who have years of study in this topic.   }{\plain \fs24 \b\f8 No worries if you miss a lesson.  You can always jump in!  Starting \softline
December 2, between the services, at 9:50 AM, facilitated by Jason Tolbert.\par
}{\plain \fs24 \b\f8 \par
}{\plain \fs24 \b\f8 THANK YOU!!! }{\plain \fs24 \f8 Living Savior and Ambiente together provided 30 families with complete (and then some) \softline
Thanksgiving Meals.  What an incredible outpouring of generosity to our neighbors in need.  The Thanksgiving \softline
"baskets" were delivered to families served by Shelter House and Artemis House/NOVACO: families who are \softline
homeless, in transitional housing, or victims of domestic violence. \par
}{\plain \fs24 \b\f8 \par
}{\plain \fs24 \b\f8 Living Savior Preschool - }{\plain \fs24 \f8 The preschool got into the Christmas spirit as they attended the Tiny Tots Concert at \softline
Robinson Secondary School to listen to the symphonic band perform. The children continue to prepare for their \softline
Christmas program here at Living Savior where they will act out the Christmas story and sing songs as a gift to \softline
their parents and friends. It is so joyful to hear all their little voices singing throughout the halls!\par
}\pard \fs24\qj\tx-540\tx0\tx720\tx1440\tx2160\tx2880\tx3600\tx4320\tx5040\tx5760\tx6480\tx7200\tx7920\tx8640\tx8910\tx9360\tx10080\tx10800\tx11520\tx12240\tx12960\tx13680\tx14400\tx15120\tx15840\tx16560\tx17280\tx18000\tx18720 
{\plain \fs24 \f8 \par
}{\plain \fs24 \b\f8 Women's Retreat! Registration deadline extended until January 1st to attend the Women's Retreat }{\plain \fs24 \f8 at the \softline
Rosyln Center the weekend of May 3-5, 2019.  Due to the success of the Holiday Bazaar, we are able to reduce \softline
the registration cost for all women attending.  Cost per person for 2 nights with 5 meals, based on double \softline
occupancy is now $260.  Sign up using the following link: https://goo.gl/forms/OmgEratpSzqSQvOt2.  Contact \softline
Wendy McGraw at teachandmentor@usa.com with questions.\par
